</taxonomicName>
deposited in the BMNH (
<figureCitation id="1CDC43CDFFF801446779F6D197D98DCA" box="[1099,1192,1745,1768]" captionStart="Figs 105–112" captionStartId="24.[151,188,1945,1964]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,333,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-13@24.[180,1408,333,1921]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figs 105–112. Habitus of species excluded from Taumacera. 105 – Fleutiauxia chinensis (Maulik, 1933) (male, syntype); 106 – F. chinensis (female, syntype of F. mutifrons Gressitt &amp; Kimoto, 1963); 107 – Hoplosaenidea abdominalis (Jacoby, 1884) (male, holotype of Platyxantha wallacei Jacoby, 1895); 108 – Hoplosaenidea dohertyi (Jacoby, 1894) (female, syntype); 109 – Hyphaenia balyi (Jacoby, 1895) (female, lectotype); 110 – Pseudoscelida nigrolimbata (Jacoby, 1899) (male, syntype); 111 – Metrioidea grandis (Allard, 1889) (male, syntype of Platyxantha robusta Jacoby, 1895); 112 – Theopella bodjoensis (Duvivier, 1885) (female, syntype of Platyxantha quadraticollis Jacoby, 1896)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4505542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4505542/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Fig. 112</figureCitation>
), MSGN, and a photograph of additional 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFF801446735F6F197288C2A" box="[1031,1113,1777,1800]" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">syntype</typeStatus>
material deposited in the MCZ were compared with the 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFF801446771F71197E78C0A" box="[1091,1174,1809,1832]" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF80144678BF71196ED8C0A" baseAuthorityName="Duvivier" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[1209,1436,1809,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Theopella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bodjoensis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF80144678BF71196ED8C0A" box="[1209,1436,1809,1832]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Theopella bodjoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
deposited in the ISNB. Both taxa are conspecific. Also, the type localities, Batu Island and Sipora Island, are located very close to one another. Both taxa were already correctly synonymized by 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF80144676FF79197868C8A" author="ASLAM N. A." box="[1117,1271,1937,1960]" firstAuthor="ASLAM" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" pagination="483 - 501" part="6" refId="ref30215" refString="ASLAM N. A. 1972: On the genus Drasa Bryant (Coleoptera, Chrysomelidae, Galerucinae) with some nomenclatorial notes on the Galerucinae. Journal of Natural History 6: 483 - 501." title="On the genus Drasa Bryant (Coleoptera, Chrysomelidae, Galerucinae) with some nomenclatorial notes on the Galerucinae" type="journal article" year="1972">ASLAM (1972)</bibRefCitation>
, however, subsequent authors (
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF8014460C8F7B197FE8CEA" author="KIMOTO S." box="[1018,1167,1969,1992]" firstAuthor="KIMOTO" journalOrPublisher="Kurume University Journal" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" pagination="201 - 237" part="39" refId="ref31701" refString="KIMOTO S. 1990: Check-list of Chrysomelidae of south east Asia, south of Thailand and west of Irian-Jaya of Indonesia, VI. Galerucinae, 2. Kurume University Journal 39: 201 - 237." title="Check-list of Chrysomelidae of south east Asia, south of Thailand and west of Irian-Jaya of Indonesia, VI. Galerucinae, 2." type="journal article" year="1990">KIMOTO 1990</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF8014467ACF7B196618CEA" author="REID C. A. M." box="[1182,1296,1969,1992]" firstAuthor="REID" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Entomology" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" pagination="1 - 9" part="38" refId="ref33192" refString="REID C. A. M. 1999: Reappraisal of the genus Taumacera Thunberg with descriptions of two new species from South-East Asia (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae). Australian Journal of Entomology 38: 1 - 9." title="Reappraisal of the genus Taumacera Thunberg with descriptions of two new species from South-East Asia (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae)" type="journal article" year="1999">REID 1999</bibRefCitation>
) overlooked this synonymy. 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF8014460D8F7D1967A8CCA" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1896" box="[1002,1291,2001,2024]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadraticollis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF8014460D8F7D1967A8CCA" box="[1002,1291,2001,2024]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Platyxantha quadraticollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confirmed as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF8014460C2F7F197A5832A" baseAuthorityName="Duvivier" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[1008,1236,2033,2056]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Theopella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bodjoensis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF8014460C2F7F197A5832A" box="[1008,1236,2033,2056]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="49">Theopella bodjoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
